<br>
To clarify, paladins and clerics can both stun anything I've seen in plane of Valor and Storms, short of named.<br>
Draught of thunder gets the immune message on anything in these planes. <br>
<br>
 <p>Master <a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=373722>Nandian</a><BR>
Arcanist of The Kindred<BR>
<BR>
I fell off the monkey bars, and when I woke up.. I was <a href=http://www.the-kindred.org>HERE</a>!</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nandiantyrael>Nandian Tyrael</A> at: 12/18/02 2:35:20 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=enoah35>Enoah35</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 494<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/17/02 2:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Draught of Thunder</span><hr size=1> Those are tagged with Stun immune. You know like giants have innate stun immunity. If the mob is stunnable then it will stun the mob till 60.<br>
<br>
Enoah <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=avgwiz>AvgWiz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/17/02 8:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Draught of Thunder</span><hr size=1> This is something that should be changed in my opinion.<br>
<br>
The stun component of this spell works up to the same level mobs as Draught of Jiva.  This reduces the upgrade this spell provides to the damage only (but with all the added aggro).  I think Verant needs to address this.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nandiantyrael>Nandian Tyrael</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/18/02 2:24 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Draught of Thunder</span><hr size=1> &quot;Those are tagged with Stun immune.&quot;<br>
Nope, it's level.  Paladins and Clerics can both stun these mobs with the 61+ stuns they get.<br>
<br>
To clarify, paladins and clerics can both stun anything I've seen in plane of Valor and Storms, short of 67+ named.<br>
Draught of thunder gets the immune message on anything in these planes. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=373722>Sage Nandian Meles`nSularis</a><BR>
Arcanist of The Kindred<BR>
<BR>
I fell off the monkey bars, and when I woke up.. I was <a href=http://www.the-kindred.org>HERE</a>!</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nandiantyrael>Nandian Tyrael</A> at: 12/18/02 2:28:01 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aiyanenfarre>Aiyane N Farre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 202<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/18/02 2:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Draught of Thunder (broken?)</span><hr size=1> Well, you're both right sorta. Mobs above level 55 are innately imune to stun. Some Cleric/Paladin/Chanter/Bard stuns are coded to ignore this and stun the mob anyway. Paladins also get an AA ability that lets them do this with any stun.<br>
<br>
I do find it rather pathetic that we got a new spell with stun component that only works on light blue or green mobs. Most likely explaination? The developer had no idea high level mobs were imune to stun and just copied DoJ info to the new spell.<br>
 <p>Aiyane N'Farre<br>
Pyrotechnic<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.ilsikhaucil.com">Ilsik Haucil</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=133769">My Profile</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gagaliya>gagaliya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 309<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/18/02 6:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Draught of Thunder (broken?)</span><hr size=1> it's a very good spell for soloing, you can hold aggro or get aggro with 1 cast most times.<br>
<br>
gaga, gnome <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nandiantyrael>Nandian Tyrael</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/18/02 9:46 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Draught of Thunder (broken?)</span><hr size=1> =/ I'd prefer either removing the stun entirely (the agro makes it useless for grouping since everything's immune to it), or allowing us to stun mobs that we fight in pop.<br>
<br>
As it is, I find it a somewhat annoying spell to use, sadly. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=373722>Sage Nandian Meles`nSularis</a><BR>
Arcanist of The Kindred<BR>
<BR>
I fell off the monkey bars, and when I woke up.. I was <a href=http://www.the-kindred.org>HERE</a>!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fraethir>Fraethir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 611<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/25/02 1:50 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Draught of Thunder (broken?)</span><hr size=1> Telekin's the first stun we have that ignores the L55 barrier, that I know of. I regularly stun things in the Plane of Justice that I think are above 55 (down int he jails) but don't have a good way to check...<br>
<br>
Aren't all of the over 60 draughts also -50 resist? Minilures? That right there makes them a significant upgrade to Draught of Jiva, even if the interrupt doesn't take. The extra damage is pretty nice too, IMO.<br>
<br>
 <p>Sutekh, Kephra, etc. Damn the html!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rombusmindspire>Rombus Mindspire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Forum Admin</font></td></tr></table><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Samadhi's Arch Nemesis</font></td></tr></table><br><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif><a href=mailto:rombus@graffe.com style=text-decoration: none><font color=#FFFFFF>Contact Rombus</font></a></font></td></tr></table></span><br>  Posts: 5950<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/25/02 10:21 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Draught of Thunder (broken?)</span><hr size=1> It's not a stun really, it's a casting interrupt component (0.0 second stun) and it works up to 60 (not 55).  The spells that Clerics and Paladins have that stun past 60 are specifically stuns (not casting interrupts) like Telekin.<br>
<br>
I wouldn't remove the stun personally.  I've found it to be quite useful in a bunch of situations.  Draught of Ro and E`Ci work in just about every situation that Draught of Thunder will work in... provided you have them! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.tritonguild.com/rombus/sig.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:Verdana;font-size:xx-small;">Officer of Triton, Member of Team Ice, Povar<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->:. <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=458434">Rombus, Arcanist</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> .:. <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5702">Rommy, 61 High Priest</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> .:</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mysthyl>Mysthyl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 485<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/27/02 4:02 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> draught of thunder</span><hr size=1> Draught of thunder is a lvl 63 spell. Most mobs 63+ players fight are all 59 and over. Doesn't make sence that this spell once obtained doesn't work on anything you are actually fighting. Change the interupt to effect all mobs that telekin lands on.<br>
<br>
Mysthyl Endowyn <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shakarr>Shakarr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/8/03 2:26 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> interrupt</span><hr size=1> If this spell interrupt component was changed to the same level as Telekin it would be extremely powerful. It's fast as hell, does decent damage and with the -50 to resists lands everytime. Try using it on the CHing (or necro) spiders in PoD...it owns them so bad it's not even funny. Would I take the change? Hell yeah, but I just don't think they will change it.<br>
<br>
As it stands, it's handy in some places but very limited.<br>
<br>
Shakarr Shockweaver<br>
65 Arcanist<br>
Bristlebane <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showPrevMessage?topicID=835.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=835.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.emailToFriend?topicID=835.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.threadControl?topicID=835.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=835.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=835.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub140.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm60">Graffe Forum News<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm1">General EQ Discussion<option value="graffeswizardcompil